# gen148 (E4): ordinary user model. Durable personal facts (name,
# possessions, preferences) are reported separately from session-only context
# (mood, current topic, constraints).
> call me Dana
< Nice to meet you, Dana!
> my dog is Rex
< Got it: your dog is Rex.
> I like jazz
< Got it: you like jazz.
> what do I like?
< You like jazz.
> I am tired
< Sounds like a low-energy moment. We can keep it light — tell me one thing that happened, or ask me something small.
> what mood am I in?
< You told me you feel tired.
> can we talk about cooking
< Sure, let's talk about cooking. What about cooking is on your mind?
> what topic are we on?
< The current topic is cooking.
> please keep it short
< Got it: I will keep it short.
> what constraint did I give you?
< Your current constraint is: keep it short.
> what do you remember about me?
< I remember: your name is Dana; your dog is Rex; you like jazz. Session context: you feel tired; current topic is cooking; constraint: keep it short.
